{
  "texts": [
    "The interstitium is filled with tiny blood capillaries that facilitate the exchange of gases between alveoli and blood.",
    "A few lung conditions that impact the interstitium are interstitial lung disease (ILD), pneumonia, and pulmonary edema.",
    "• Blood-Vessels-Related Lung Diseases: Low-oxygen blood is pumped into the right side of the heart through veins.",
    "It uses the pulmonary arteries to push blood into your lungs.",
    "These blood vessels can also acquire diseases."
  ]
}